WEBVTT

00:03.537 --> 00:06.206
WALSH: Job came in about
an hour ago from sanitation.

00:06.206 --> 00:08.141
DANNY: There was nothing else?
Just the head?

00:08.141 --> 00:11.812
So far. M.E.'s office
is on the way.

00:11.812 --> 00:13.313
Pretty decomposed.

00:13.313 --> 00:16.116
Why don't you go on up there
and have a closer look?

00:16.116 --> 00:18.318
He just said M.E.'s on the way.

00:18.318 --> 00:20.854
I'll look out
for them. Go on.

00:26.193 --> 00:27.861
When you were
taking the test,

00:27.861 --> 00:29.997
you ever think you'd be
climbing up a pile of garbage

00:29.997 --> 00:31.698
to get to a severed head?

00:31.698 --> 00:33.934
No. Thought I'd be more like

00:33.934 --> 00:37.504
Paul Newman
in Fort Apache, The Bronx.

00:37.504 --> 00:39.373
It was Cagney & Lacey for me.

00:39.373 --> 00:41.208
You know we could just retire,

00:41.208 --> 00:43.844
and go to a tropical island
and solve crimes there.

00:43.844 --> 00:45.112
We could,
but you would

00:45.112 --> 00:46.847
never survive outside
the five boroughs.

00:46.847 --> 00:48.348
That's true.

00:50.751 --> 00:51.985
Yeah, it's Mano Sangriento.

00:51.985 --> 00:53.320
Black hand?

00:53.320 --> 00:56.523
No, just the fingers.
But it was a hand.

00:56.523 --> 00:57.925
That's the calling card.

00:57.925 --> 00:59.459
Yeah. Now we're gonna
have to figure out

00:59.459 --> 01:01.662
why this guy lost his head.

01:01.662 --> 01:05.299
Jose Cortez, 30,
from Sunset Park.

01:05.299 --> 01:08.535
Cops found him in possession
of a half-ounce of cocaine.

01:08.535 --> 01:10.837
ERIN: Criminal possession
in the third degree.

01:10.837 --> 01:12.606
But Cortez has no priors,
so he's eligible

01:12.606 --> 01:14.007
for judicial diversion.

01:14.007 --> 01:17.277
So he'll get drug treatment
instead of jail time.

01:17.277 --> 01:19.379
And Schneiderman is on deck, so
no doubt she'll recommend rehab.

01:19.379 --> 01:21.415
You run a triple I check
to make sure he doesn't have

01:21.415 --> 01:22.749
a record outside of New York?

01:22.749 --> 01:25.319
His record's clean.
Legal aid's gonna ask for R.O.R.

01:25.319 --> 01:26.987
What do you want to do?

01:26.987 --> 01:28.388
I'll ask for 500 bail.

01:28.388 --> 01:29.890
She'll R.O.R. him anyway.

01:29.890 --> 01:31.291
And so it goes.

01:31.291 --> 01:32.926
All right, well, you seem to
have everything under control.

01:32.926 --> 01:34.094
You need anything from me?

01:34.094 --> 01:35.128
A raise.

01:35.128 --> 01:37.564
Get in line.

01:41.668 --> 01:43.670
You want some breakfast?

01:43.670 --> 01:46.340
Kale and protein powder?
I think I'll pass.

01:46.340 --> 01:47.774
If you show me what's under
that robe, I'll make you

01:47.774 --> 01:49.443
whatever you want.
Well, in that case,

01:49.443 --> 01:52.479
you're gonna have to produce
some pretty killer pancakes.

01:52.479 --> 01:54.047
Mm-hmm.

01:56.183 --> 01:58.051
Wish I didn't have court.

01:58.051 --> 02:01.388
Mm. It's better than being stuck
in Jersey traffic.

02:01.388 --> 02:03.256
No, I mean, I wish
I could come with you.

02:03.256 --> 02:04.925
It's no biggie.

02:04.925 --> 02:06.727
Telling your mom that
we're engaged is a biggie.

02:06.727 --> 02:08.328
Mm...
Plus, I haven't
even met her yet.

02:08.328 --> 02:10.797
Exactly. Let's keep it that way.

02:10.797 --> 02:11.865
What does that mean?

02:11.865 --> 02:15.302
My mother has scared off

02:15.302 --> 02:17.904
every boyfriend
I've ever introduced her to.

02:17.904 --> 02:19.940
I'm not every boyfriend.

02:19.940 --> 02:22.809
Well, then you'll see
for yourself when you meet her.

02:22.809 --> 02:24.144
At the wedding.

02:25.545 --> 02:27.314
Ridiculous.

02:30.350 --> 02:32.386
Eddie, great news. My court date
got pushed to tomorrow.

02:32.386 --> 02:33.920
Oh.

02:33.920 --> 02:36.156
I can come with you.
Wait, what?

02:36.156 --> 02:38.191
Yeah, I'll just take the
day and come with you.

02:38.191 --> 02:40.327
No, definitely not.

02:43.430 --> 02:46.600
Invisibility.
Definitely invisibility.

02:46.600 --> 02:48.769
No, man. Spidey-sense.

02:48.769 --> 02:51.204
Then, you get fair warning
when something's gonna go down.

02:51.204 --> 02:53.507
How about X

02:53.507 --> 02:56.243
Ugh, no. There are things
I don't want to see.

02:56.243 --> 02:59.312
I've always had a thing
for the Lasso of Truth.

02:59.312 --> 03:02.315
Come in handy when
we make detective.

03:11.058 --> 03:12.726
Hey, why do you guys
always weigh the brain?

03:12.726 --> 03:14.261
To see how much they weigh.

03:14.261 --> 03:17.097
Actually, it's to look
for abnormalities.

03:17.097 --> 03:18.565
This one is

03:18.565 --> 03:20.033
three pounds
of memories, emotions

03:20.033 --> 03:22.636
and 86 billion nerve cells.

03:22.636 --> 03:25.639
Hmm.
I've always wondered about the
part that controls your emotion.

03:25.639 --> 03:27.207
Oh, the amygdala.

03:27.207 --> 03:29.209
Kind of wish I could have it
removed sometimes.

03:29.209 --> 03:30.610
Yeah, but then you'd
be a serial killer.

03:30.610 --> 03:31.778
Uh, what can you
tell us about

03:31.778 --> 03:33.146
the head you found
at the garbage dump?

03:33.146 --> 03:36.349
I'm waiting on DNA, but the time
of death and the injuries

03:36.349 --> 03:38.351
are consistent
with that headless corpse

03:38.351 --> 03:39.986
you guys brought me
a few weeks ago.

03:39.986 --> 03:42.255
You mean the one belonging
to Luis Delgado?

03:42.255 --> 03:44.491
That body wasn't Luis Delgado.

03:44.491 --> 03:45.892
What are you talking about?

03:45.892 --> 03:48.762
That body and the head that
you pulled out from the garbage

03:48.762 --> 03:50.831
this morning appear
to belong to the same person.

03:50.831 --> 03:52.499
No, the body
we found on the beach

03:52.499 --> 03:55.569
with Luis Delgado's clothes on
and Luis Delgado's tattoos

03:55.569 --> 03:57.137
belong to Luis Delgado.

03:57.137 --> 03:58.472
Trust me.

03:58.472 --> 04:01.274
I had to get dental records
from Mexico to confirm.

04:01.274 --> 04:03.610
Great. Then the son of a bitch

04:03.610 --> 04:06.146
who burned down my house
is still alive.

04:18.492 --> 04:20.427
What is it?

04:20.427 --> 04:23.830
Two officers sitting
on a witness's house

04:23.830 --> 04:26.600
were shot multiple times
inside their patrol car.

04:26.600 --> 04:27.901
Both critical.

04:27.901 --> 04:30.537
Anyone likely?
Information's
still coming in.

04:30.537 --> 04:32.639
They're at Saint Irene's.

04:32.639 --> 04:34.007
And the shooter?

04:34.007 --> 04:35.142
No word yet.

04:35.142 --> 04:38.145
Frank, one of the officers

04:38.145 --> 04:40.881
is Abigail's husband.

