Hey.

05:24.057 --> 05:25.725
Two cops were shot
in their patrol car.

05:25.725 --> 05:27.561
I heard. Any word
on their condition?

05:27.561 --> 05:29.596
Still waiting. But Erin,

05:29.596 --> 05:31.932
they just picked up
the shooter.

05:31.932 --> 05:33.867
It's Jose Cortez.

05:35.969 --> 05:37.504
The guy we released
this morning?

05:37.504 --> 05:39.539
He went straight from
arraignment court

05:39.539 --> 05:42.108
to his apartment,
he picked up a .45

05:42.108 --> 05:45.312
and he opened fire. He's got
a record for murder and assault.

05:45.312 --> 05:47.781
No. His rap sheet came up empty.

05:47.781 --> 05:49.216
It came up empty
in our system

05:49.216 --> 05:51.851
because his priors
were in Mexico.

05:51.851 --> 05:54.688
Anthony, this is my fault.

05:54.688 --> 05:56.022
No.

05:56.022 --> 05:58.491
Your A.D.A. followed
the bail recommendations

05:58.491 --> 05:59.492
to the letter.

05:59.492 --> 06:00.727
Tell that to the two cops

06:00.727 --> 06:02.262
laying in the hospital.

06:41.501 --> 06:43.336
Officer Davis is out of surgery.

06:43.336 --> 06:45.472
He's in recovery.

06:45.472 --> 06:47.807
Brian took a bullet to his neck,

06:47.807 --> 06:49.709
which severed his jugular.

06:53.980 --> 06:56.716
Did I ever show you
Brian's department photo?

07:04.557 --> 07:07.627
You're not supposed to,
but... he smiled.

07:07.627 --> 07:09.963
On purpose.

07:09.963 --> 07:12.365
He said every time
you see a cop shot

07:12.365 --> 07:14.100
on the front page of the paper,

07:14.100 --> 07:17.637
it's always the official photo
and they look so serious.

07:17.637 --> 07:20.106
He figured if he smiled,
it was...

07:20.106 --> 07:23.543
some sort of guarantee that
nothing bad would happen to him.

07:26.980 --> 07:30.250
He might be right.

07:30.250 --> 07:34.554
I've promised him all kinds
of things if he gets better.

07:54.140 --> 07:56.009
Brian,

07:56.009 --> 07:59.346
it's Commissioner Reagan.

08:19.799 --> 08:22.602
Whatever it takes, Abigail.

08:27.741 --> 08:29.075
DANNY:
I'm telling you,

08:29.075 --> 08:31.277
Delgado had this guy
made up to look like him,

08:31.277 --> 08:32.812
even down to the tattoo,

08:32.812 --> 08:34.481
so he could pull
one over on us.

08:34.481 --> 08:37.684
Mano Sangriento is all over
Long Island and Manhattan now.

08:37.684 --> 08:39.753
They all use
the black hand.
He played us.

08:39.753 --> 08:42.956
I've checked every ship
and airline passenger list.

08:42.956 --> 08:44.124
I don't think he left town.

08:44.124 --> 08:45.458
Look, it's been weeks, okay?

08:45.458 --> 08:47.460
He could be anywhere by
now, including Mexico.

08:47.460 --> 08:49.195
Just speak to the DEA.

08:49.195 --> 08:50.864
See if they'll give you
anything they got on him.

08:50.864 --> 08:52.999
I'll check the warrant my sister
gave me on his cell phone

08:52.999 --> 08:55.201
and see if that
turns anything up.

09:02.742 --> 09:05.678
I think someone else
should find Delgado.

09:05.678 --> 09:07.280
It's way too personal

09:07.280 --> 09:09.315
between you and him.
I'm not gonna go

09:09.315 --> 09:11.151
off the rails, if that's
what you're thinking, okay?

09:11.151 --> 09:12.152
I promise.

09:12.152 --> 09:13.253
You already did.

09:13.253 --> 09:15.221
Do you really want to put us
in the crosshairs?

09:15.221 --> 09:16.556
Look, I'm gonna get
that son of a bitch,

09:16.556 --> 09:17.924
no matter what it takes.

09:20.827 --> 09:22.695
You don't want
to be a part of that,

09:22.695 --> 09:25.165
then I suggest
you walk away on this one.

09:25.165 --> 09:27.333
You really want me to walk away?

09:46.519 --> 09:48.588
JANKO:
Mom.

09:48.588 --> 09:49.989
Hi.

09:49.989 --> 09:52.392
Hi.

09:52.392 --> 09:54.227
Hmm.
This is Jamie.

09:55.728 --> 09:58.064
Hi.
You didn't tell me
you were bringing someone.

09:58.064 --> 10:00.133
I know. I'm sorry.
Jamie Reagan.
Nice to meet you.

10:00.133 --> 10:01.301
How do you do?

10:01.301 --> 10:02.235
Very well.

10:03.837 --> 10:05.338
You're welcome.

10:05.338 --> 10:06.673
Um...
Can I steal this?

10:06.673 --> 10:07.941
Yes, no problem.

10:12.912 --> 10:15.782
So...

10:15.782 --> 10:17.117
are you dating?

10:17.117 --> 10:19.686
Is this, like,
a new boyfriend?

10:19.686 --> 10:21.921
Uh, he-he's my fiancÃ©.

10:21.921 --> 10:25.024
FiancÃ©?

10:25.024 --> 10:27.093
And this is the first time
I'm meeting you?

10:27.093 --> 10:28.962
Well, we didn't
really date date.

10:28.962 --> 10:30.096
You didn't date?

10:30.096 --> 10:31.231
What he means
is we've known each other

10:31.231 --> 10:32.565
for a long time.

10:32.565 --> 10:34.267
We were partners on the job.

10:34.267 --> 10:37.103
So you're a cop.

10:37.103 --> 10:38.104
He's a sergeant.

10:41.574 --> 10:43.243
He went to Harvard.

10:43.243 --> 10:46.546
A quarter of a million dollars
in tuition

10:46.546 --> 10:48.581
and you decided to be a cop.

10:48.581 --> 10:49.749
Well, my whole family's
in law enforcement,

10:49.749 --> 10:51.518
so I guess it was in the blood.

10:51.518 --> 10:53.620
It's too bad doctor or lawyer
wasn't in the blood.

10:53.620 --> 10:54.954
Then you two could

10:54.954 --> 10:57.824
actually afford
a nice lifestyle.

10:57.824 --> 10:59.492
We love our lifestyle, Mom.

10:59.492 --> 11:00.693
Do you own a house?

11:00.693 --> 11:02.328
I have an apartment.

11:02.328 --> 11:03.563
Eddie likes being in the city.

11:03.563 --> 11:06.032
"Eddie"?
No one calls me
Edit, Mom.

11:06.032 --> 11:08.735
I do. Your father does.

11:08.735 --> 11:11.070
Well, I like Eddie.

11:11.070 --> 11:13.606
So, you use a boy's name
and he uses a girl's name.

11:13.606 --> 11:14.507
Mom.

11:14.507 --> 11:16.709
:
I'm just saying.

11:16.709 --> 11:18.745
That's okay.
My real name's Jameson.

11:18.745 --> 11:19.979
Like the whiskey.

11:19.979 --> 11:21.881
Yeah, like the whiskey.

11:21.881 --> 11:24.350
It's a good thing your parents
didn't like to drink Smirnoff.

11:24.350 --> 11:26.886
Mom.
What?

11:29.255 --> 11:32.592
So, Reagan, is that, is that
any relation to...

11:32.592 --> 11:34.227
The police commissioner,
yes, he's my dad.

11:36.329 --> 11:37.497
What?

11:37.497 --> 11:39.599
You must see the humor
in this, Edit.

11:39.599 --> 11:41.234
Your father's in jail,

11:41.234 --> 11:44.270
and you're marrying
the police commissioner's son.

11:45.872 --> 11:48.875
That's going to make for some
very interesting conversation

11:48.875 --> 11:50.910
at the wedding reception,
don't you think?

11:57.550 --> 12:01.287
Looks like Davis has permanent
nerve damage to his hand.

12:02.355 --> 12:04.224
GORMLEY:
His shooting hand,

12:04.224 --> 12:07.427
so he'll be off
the street for good.
Well, not necessarily.

12:07.427 --> 12:10.530
Not with the kind of things
they can do today.

12:10.530 --> 12:12.532
And Brian Baker?

12:13.633 --> 12:15.435
Still the same.

12:15.435 --> 12:17.437
A.D.A. Reagan, boss.

12:22.108 --> 12:24.043
GORMLEY:
Erin.

12:24.043 --> 12:25.411
Garrett. Sid.

12:25.411 --> 12:27.213
Erin.
How's Brian?

12:27.213 --> 12:29.215
Still unconscious.

12:29.215 --> 12:32.018
It's a waiting game right now.

12:32.018 --> 12:34.420
And Abigail?

12:34.420 --> 12:37.056
Abigail hasn't left his side.

12:40.994 --> 12:42.929
Where's your boss?

12:44.163 --> 12:47.166
He's not coming.

12:49.535 --> 12:52.438
Okay.

12:52.438 --> 12:55.008
I'll be in my office, boss.

13:03.116 --> 13:05.418
Cortez was my case.
I supervised it.

13:05.418 --> 13:07.320
It was my responsibility.

13:07.320 --> 13:10.390
What were you thinking
letting him walk?

13:10.390 --> 13:12.525
He didn't walk.
He made bail.

13:12.525 --> 13:15.261
Bail was set at 500 bucks, Erin.
Of course he walked.

13:15.261 --> 13:17.497
That's chump change
for a drug dealer.

13:17.497 --> 13:21.167
The arrest was
for a nonviolent drug charge.

13:21.167 --> 13:22.869
We are not in the business
of asking

13:22.869 --> 13:25.772
for high bail because we think
someone might become dangerous.

13:25.772 --> 13:29.942
He has a felony record
in Mexico: murder, assault.

13:29.942 --> 13:32.912
My office didn't have access
to that information.

13:34.247 --> 13:36.282
So the D.A.'s office

13:36.282 --> 13:38.351
is in a rush to hold his hand,

13:38.351 --> 13:41.521
and he goes out
and shoots two of my cops.

13:42.588 --> 13:44.824
What do you want me to say, Dad?

13:44.824 --> 13:48.394
The department policy is to ask
for little or no bail

13:48.394 --> 13:50.496
for nonviolent crimes.

13:50.496 --> 13:53.132
The policy has had success.

13:54.233 --> 13:56.002
Not so much.

