of money terrorizing people.

15:01.300 --> 15:03.002
Who's terrorizing who?

15:03.002 --> 15:04.504
Get the phone.
Pick it up.

15:04.504 --> 15:06.506
Call your husband.
Come on.

15:06.506 --> 15:08.374
Turn around.

15:08.374 --> 15:10.777
Don't do anything crazy.

15:14.514 --> 15:16.215
Luis?

15:17.583 --> 15:19.185
Hey, remember me?

15:19.185 --> 15:21.120
Where's Isabel?
She's right here.

15:21.120 --> 15:22.855
Kids are here, too.
But don't worry, they're safe.

15:22.855 --> 15:24.991
Unless, of course,
I decide to burn your house down

15:24.991 --> 15:26.359
like you burned down mine.

15:26.359 --> 15:27.660
If you harm them,

15:27.660 --> 15:30.797
I swear I'll kill you.

15:30.797 --> 15:33.499
Well, then you better
hurry up and get home.

15:33.499 --> 15:34.634
Sit down.

15:44.410 --> 15:46.212
Officer Davis took a bullet
to his right hand,

15:46.212 --> 15:48.414
which has caused
permanent nerve damage.

15:48.414 --> 15:50.983
Officer Baker was hit
with a bullet in his neck,

15:50.983 --> 15:53.052
which punctured his jugular.

15:53.052 --> 15:57.790
The bullet was removed, but he
has not regained consciousness.

15:57.790 --> 16:00.126
We will have updates
as things progress.

16:01.527 --> 16:02.829
What about the shooter?

16:02.829 --> 16:04.397
Uh, the shooter,
Jose Cortez,

16:04.397 --> 16:06.666
was apprehended
shortly after the shooting.

16:06.666 --> 16:08.167
He has been charged

16:08.167 --> 16:09.902
with attempted murder
in the first degree

16:09.902 --> 16:12.104
and will be arraigned
later this afternoon.

16:12.104 --> 16:14.407
Initial reports said Cortez
had been arrested before,

16:14.407 --> 16:16.142
but released on bail.
That's correct.

16:16.142 --> 16:18.411
He was arrested for
drug possession

16:18.411 --> 16:20.079
and released on bail
this morning.

16:20.079 --> 16:22.148
MAN:
Why was he released on bail?

16:22.148 --> 16:23.583
The nonviolent nature
of his crimes

16:23.583 --> 16:25.651
and the lack
of prior criminal history.

16:25.651 --> 16:28.221
Why was he released
in the first place?
He was a member of Mano Sangriento.

16:28.221 --> 16:30.456
Mr. Cortez had
no criminal history

16:30.456 --> 16:32.692
or gang affiliation
on record.

16:32.692 --> 16:34.360
It was handled

16:34.360 --> 16:35.394
as a first-time offense.

16:35.394 --> 16:36.963
What do you mean, "on record"?

16:36.963 --> 16:39.632
Mr. Cortez had
a prior record in Mexico

16:39.632 --> 16:43.436
that did not come up
on the initial background check.

16:43.436 --> 16:45.438
In light of what happened,
is the D.A.'s office

16:45.438 --> 16:46.806
going to rethink this policy?

16:46.806 --> 16:50.977
The policy was established
to decrease overcrowded prisons

16:50.977 --> 16:52.645
filled with
nonviolent offenders.

16:52.645 --> 16:56.249
In this regard,
the policy is a success.

16:56.249 --> 16:59.518
The NYPD has two good officers
in the hospital,

16:59.518 --> 17:01.721
one facing disability,

17:01.721 --> 17:03.956
one may not survive.

17:03.956 --> 17:06.459
Asking for minimum bail

17:06.459 --> 17:08.728
for felonies
puts my officers

17:08.728 --> 17:10.529
and, more importantly,

17:10.529 --> 17:12.131
our citizens at risk,

17:12.131 --> 17:15.268
because these criminals
will then be incentivized

17:15.268 --> 17:17.570
to go out and commit more,

17:17.570 --> 17:19.272
worse crimes.

17:19.272 --> 17:21.340
And that is exactly
what happened today.

17:23.175 --> 17:25.044
GARRETT:
That's all.

17:25.044 --> 17:26.312
Thank you.
Thank you very much.

17:33.286 --> 17:34.587
I don't know how you
actually thought

17:34.587 --> 17:35.855
you could avoid me
meeting your mother.

17:35.855 --> 17:38.190
Oh, I was doing a great job
avoiding until today.

17:38.190 --> 17:40.026
Eddie, you've met my whole
family; they're not perfect.

17:40.026 --> 17:42.828
You have... you know, you have
a Norman Rockwell family.

17:42.828 --> 17:44.997
You go to church on Sundays,
and you eat together on Sundays.

17:44.997 --> 17:46.766
Just please don't.

17:46.766 --> 17:48.834
Just saying, it doesn't
bother me what she says.

17:48.834 --> 17:51.504
She just has no filter.

17:51.504 --> 17:52.805
And she only cares

17:52.805 --> 17:54.340
about money.

17:54.340 --> 17:56.475
Eddie, do you know why we have
family dinner every Sunday?

17:56.475 --> 17:57.910
No. Why?

17:57.910 --> 18:00.947
Because my grandmother grew up
poor in a small town in Ireland.

18:00.947 --> 18:02.581
She was the oldest of 12 kids,

18:02.581 --> 18:04.317
and there was never
enough to eat.

18:04.317 --> 18:06.319
She moved to New York
to make money.

18:06.319 --> 18:08.487
She met my grandpa, and
when they got married,

18:08.487 --> 18:10.089
she promised herself
that they would always

18:10.089 --> 18:11.891
have more than enough to eat.

18:11.891 --> 18:13.392
Family dinner was

18:13.392 --> 18:16.195
just her way of proudly
proving that every week.

18:17.863 --> 18:22.768
That meal was so important to
her because of how she grew up.

18:22.768 --> 18:25.137
I'm just saying, there must be
some deep-seated reason

18:25.137 --> 18:27.239
why your mother is
so obsessed about money.

18:27.239 --> 18:31.043
My mother chooses to insult me

18:31.043 --> 18:34.480
and to insult every person
I've ever brought home.

