18:51.030 --> 18:53.065
Yeah.
Leave the car there

18:53.065 --> 18:54.533
and walk to the garage.

19:07.246 --> 19:08.614
Welcome home.

19:08.614 --> 19:09.982
Come on in.

19:11.083 --> 19:12.885
Right over there.

19:16.989 --> 19:18.424
Keep your hands where

19:18.424 --> 19:20.726
I can see 'em.
Where's my wife and my boys?

19:20.726 --> 19:23.863
Why'd you set my house on fire?

19:23.863 --> 19:25.297
You're really pretending
to be an innocent victim?

19:25.297 --> 19:27.800
:
Who gave you the order?
Doesn't matter.

19:27.800 --> 19:29.735
You think if you
take him down, it's over?

19:29.735 --> 19:31.437
You guys thought
you got El Chapo.

19:31.437 --> 19:33.673
There's 20 guys lining up
to be the next El Chapo.

19:33.673 --> 19:35.541
That's how
these organizations work.

19:35.541 --> 19:38.377
How this works is that I'm
gonna find every son of a bitch

19:38.377 --> 19:40.680
who had a hand in setting
my house on fire,

19:40.680 --> 19:42.915
and I'm not gonna stop until
every one of them's behind bars,

19:42.915 --> 19:44.316
or worse.

19:44.316 --> 19:45.985
That's how it works.

19:45.985 --> 19:47.653
Won't bring your wife back.

19:49.655 --> 19:51.190
You have two sons.

19:51.190 --> 19:54.260
You really want
to put them in danger?

19:57.329 --> 19:58.964
Baez, I got Delgado.

19:58.964 --> 20:00.066
Request a 10-85

20:00.066 --> 20:03.302
to 12 Bayview Avenue.

20:03.302 --> 20:04.603
You're under arrest.
Turn around.

20:04.603 --> 20:06.939
Put your hands
behind your back.

20:11.243 --> 20:13.045
You made a big mistake.

20:13.045 --> 20:15.147
You're the one making
a mistake, bro.

20:15.147 --> 20:16.749
I'm one of you.
Yeah?

20:16.749 --> 20:18.250
How's that?

20:19.351 --> 20:21.020
I'm working for the DEA.

20:35.634 --> 20:37.736
We have you

20:37.736 --> 20:39.505
for the murder
of Melissa Sanchez.

20:39.505 --> 20:41.373
No, you don't.
DANNY:
Yes, we do.

20:41.373 --> 20:43.709
You told me you killed her
and her unborn baby.

20:43.709 --> 20:45.711
I told you
I didn't think she was okay.

20:45.711 --> 20:47.746
As it turns out, I was right.

20:47.746 --> 20:50.416
She wasn't okay. She was dead.

20:51.584 --> 20:53.886
And Manny Sanchez.

20:55.821 --> 20:57.723
Reagan, what do you think
you're doing?

20:57.723 --> 20:59.391
What the hell do you think
you're doing?

20:59.391 --> 21:00.826
Can I talk to you outside?

21:08.300 --> 21:09.535
What the hell are you doing
here? And more importantly,

21:09.535 --> 21:10.603
what the hell
are you doing working

21:10.603 --> 21:12.338
with a scumbag like Delgado?

21:12.338 --> 21:13.873
We made a deal with him.
Yeah, I know you did.

21:13.873 --> 21:15.674
You made a deal
with a cold-blooded killer

21:15.674 --> 21:18.043
who murdered an innocent woman
and her unborn baby.

21:18.043 --> 21:21.247
Delgado's a hired hand.
We're after JosÃ© Rojas.

21:21.247 --> 21:23.516
His boss. La Almeja. The Clam.

21:23.516 --> 21:25.851
Okay.
Delgado is a hired gun.

21:25.851 --> 21:30.156
Rojas has murdered or ordered
the murder of hundreds.

21:30.156 --> 21:33.125
Okay? We get Rojas,
we bring down the organization.

21:33.125 --> 21:34.460
Great, then go get him.

21:34.460 --> 21:36.328
I already got Delgado.
He's mine.

21:36.328 --> 21:38.464
No, you're gonna back off.

21:38.464 --> 21:39.798
Go to hell.

21:39.798 --> 21:43.035
Look, I get that this
has gotten personal for you.

21:43.035 --> 21:44.503
Don't go there.
Okay, but we don't need you

21:44.503 --> 21:47.907
going in there, being a hothead,
blowing our case.

21:47.907 --> 21:50.242
I arrested Delgado.
It's my collar.

21:50.242 --> 21:52.511
Are you kidding me right now?
I got him on murder
charges. Okay?

21:52.511 --> 21:55.147
That trumps any drug charge
you could possibly get.

21:55.147 --> 21:57.082
So unless you want
to go before a judge

21:57.082 --> 21:58.918
and try to get him
to give you a writ for me

21:58.918 --> 22:00.753
to turn him over to the feds,
so be it. You go do that.

22:00.753 --> 22:03.022
But until such time,
Delgado's mine.

22:03.022 --> 22:04.356
He stays here with me.

22:04.356 --> 22:06.292
Hey.

22:08.060 --> 22:09.428
What?

22:09.428 --> 22:11.230
Maybe we can work together
on this.

22:12.364 --> 22:13.599
Well, it's the only way

22:13.599 --> 22:15.701
we're both gonna get
what we want.

22:21.607 --> 22:22.841
ALL: Bless us, O Lord,
and these Thy gifts,

22:22.841 --> 22:24.977
which we are about to receive
from Thy bounty,

22:24.977 --> 22:27.980
through Christ our Lord. Amen.

22:38.791 --> 22:42.428
You mind, uh, passing
me the mac and cheese?
Sure.

22:42.428 --> 22:44.430
Here you go.

22:44.430 --> 22:45.531
Looks good.

22:47.199 --> 22:48.701
And what's the matter
with Daniel?

22:48.701 --> 22:50.836
Nothing.

22:50.836 --> 22:52.538
Well, you're not piling food
onto your plate,

22:52.538 --> 22:54.106
so it must be something.

22:54.106 --> 22:55.708
Well, I kind of lost my appetite

22:55.708 --> 22:57.710
when I learned that the guy
who burned our house down

22:57.710 --> 22:59.712
cut a deal with the DEA.

22:59.712 --> 23:01.513
You know who burned
our house down?

23:01.513 --> 23:04.149
DANNY: Yeah.
We'll talk about it later.

23:04.149 --> 23:07.519
In the meantime, that guy's
walking around free as a bird.

23:07.519 --> 23:09.655
Well, you could always
blame the D.A.'s office.

23:09.655 --> 23:12.725
It seems to be the common
dumping ground around here.

23:12.725 --> 23:14.927
HENRY:
No one's dumping

23:14.927 --> 23:16.395
on the D.A.'s office.

23:16.395 --> 23:17.730
NICKY:
You saw

23:17.730 --> 23:19.098
the joint press conference.

23:19.098 --> 23:21.166
System's broken.
Somebody had to call it out.

23:21.166 --> 23:22.668
And here I thought
a press conference

23:22.668 --> 23:24.203
was for dispensing information,

23:24.203 --> 23:26.705
not calling people out.
My mistake.

23:26.705 --> 23:29.108
DANNY: Well, last I heard,
you commit a crime,

23:29.108 --> 23:31.443
you suffer the consequences,
end of story.

23:31.443 --> 23:33.812
You know how many times
you and Jamie have come to me

23:33.812 --> 23:35.648
for a search warrant
or a subpoena,

23:35.648 --> 23:37.616
and you haven't had everything
to get it?

23:37.616 --> 23:38.851
Yeah, about as many times

23:38.851 --> 23:40.286
as you've said no.

23:40.286 --> 23:42.021
SEAN: I'm sorry,
I still don't understand.

23:42.021 --> 23:43.789
If you know who burned
our house down,

23:43.789 --> 23:45.524
then why is he
still walking?

23:45.524 --> 23:48.027
It's something called
judicial perversion.

23:48.027 --> 23:49.295
JAMIE:
Judicial diversion.

23:49.295 --> 23:50.796
It's a policy

23:50.796 --> 23:53.799
where nonviolent offenders
get reduced bail

23:53.799 --> 23:57.069
and rehab, community service
instead of jail time.

23:57.069 --> 23:59.838
It's called
mollycoddling criminals.

23:59.838 --> 24:01.140
Exactly.
NICKY:
Is there anything

24:01.140 --> 24:03.142
that you guys don't blame
on the attorneys?

24:03.142 --> 24:04.543
Well, I'm afraid at the moment,

24:04.543 --> 24:06.412
there happens
to be plenty to blame.

24:06.412 --> 24:07.446
Amen to that.

24:07.446 --> 24:08.881
HENRY:
That's what you get for having

24:08.881 --> 24:11.450
a liberal D.A.
and a liberal mayor.

24:11.450 --> 24:13.152
Like cops don't
make mistakes?

24:13.152 --> 24:15.487
Nobody's saying that.

24:15.487 --> 24:17.022
JAMIE: To be fair, I understand
why he got a reduced bail.

24:17.022 --> 24:19.458
His arrest wasn't
for a large felony weight.

24:19.458 --> 24:21.827
Well, how about his affiliation
with an illegal gang?

24:21.827 --> 24:24.229
Or his criminal record
in Mexico?

24:24.229 --> 24:25.631
His criminal record
in Mexico

24:25.631 --> 24:27.733
doesn't come up in
a background check.

24:27.733 --> 24:29.168
It would if you ran him
through Interpol.

24:29.168 --> 24:31.203
ERIN: Why would I run
a low-level drug dealer

24:31.203 --> 24:32.237
through Interpol?

24:32.237 --> 24:33.272
Why wouldn't you?

24:37.543 --> 24:40.112
You know, when I first started
coming to these family dinners

24:40.112 --> 24:43.449
and you guys would argue,
I would get really nervous

24:43.449 --> 24:46.819
'cause I thought maybe you'd
never talk to each other again.

24:46.819 --> 24:48.654
But...

24:48.654 --> 24:50.255
you do.

24:50.255 --> 24:53.158
You just keep talking.

24:53.158 --> 24:55.928
Come hell or high water.

24:55.928 --> 24:57.463
You saying we talk too much?

24:57.463 --> 24:59.999
No.

24:59.999 --> 25:01.667
Well, don't worry, Eddie.

25:01.667 --> 25:04.670
No matter what you do,
you're golden at this table.

25:04.670 --> 25:06.605
I am?

25:06.605 --> 25:09.375
As long as you wear NYPD blue.

25:29.795 --> 25:31.764
I didn't know
you were coming here.

25:31.764 --> 25:33.265
Edit never called me.

25:33.265 --> 25:35.401
I didn't tell her.

25:35.401 --> 25:37.569
May I come in?

25:42.808 --> 25:45.043
I bet she's mad at me.

25:45.043 --> 25:46.278
Well, why wouldn't she be?

25:46.278 --> 25:47.913
She came to give you
some good news,

25:47.913 --> 25:49.214
and you rained on her parade.

25:49.214 --> 25:51.884
The good news would've been
she's marrying someone

25:51.884 --> 25:54.753
who could afford to give her
the life that she's used to.

25:54.753 --> 25:56.088
And what life would that be?

25:56.088 --> 25:58.724
One where your husband's
in prison for fraud

25:58.724 --> 26:00.592
and she wants to cut you
out of her life?

26:00.592 --> 26:02.428
She should be grateful.

26:02.428 --> 26:04.196
We gave her everything.

26:04.196 --> 26:06.799
Your husband cheated people
out of their savings.

26:06.799 --> 26:09.835
You insulted every guy
she ever brought around.

26:09.835 --> 26:11.570
I tell the truth.

26:11.570 --> 26:13.172
And the truth about me
is I don't make

26:13.172 --> 26:15.140
enough money? I'm
the wrong religion?

26:15.140 --> 26:16.241
I live in the wrong borough?

26:16.241 --> 26:17.443
I won't apologize

26:17.443 --> 26:19.077
for wanting what's best
for my daughter.

26:19.077 --> 26:21.647
I'm what's best
for your daughter.
Oh, because you love her?

26:21.647 --> 26:24.316
And that's gonna
take care of the bills?

26:24.316 --> 26:27.453
I live a comfortable life,
and my family will, too.

26:27.453 --> 26:29.822
Will it meet your standards?
I don't know.

26:29.822 --> 26:32.257
But my family
will always come first.

26:32.257 --> 26:34.760
That sounds great
on a Hallmark card.

26:34.760 --> 26:36.695
But in reality?

26:38.564 --> 26:40.466
Not so much.

26:41.800 --> 26:45.304
I don't want Edit to end up...

26:45.304 --> 26:46.572
Like you did?

26:48.607 --> 26:49.608
Maybe you need to see the world

26:49.608 --> 26:51.043
through a different set
of glasses.

26:51.043 --> 26:54.980
Well, I certainly don't trust
the rose-colored ones you wear.

26:54.980 --> 26:57.216
You haven't tried them on yet.

27:07.226 --> 27:09.461
I'm in the middle
of pretrial hearings, Pop.

27:10.562 --> 27:13.432
You call me
out here for this.

27:13.432 --> 27:16.034
I made you your
favorite sandwich.

27:16.034 --> 27:19.104
Thank you. Now,
what are we doing out here?

27:19.104 --> 27:20.439
Getting you out
of the office.

27:20.439 --> 27:23.108
My office is not
the problem. Dad is.

27:23.108 --> 27:25.577
Oh, is he, now

27:25.577 --> 27:27.379
'Cause he says
what he feels?

27:27.379 --> 27:29.781
In front of
millions of viewers

27:29.781 --> 27:32.017
at my first press conference
as bureau chief?

27:32.017 --> 27:33.585
Yeah, he could've
tempered it down.

27:33.585 --> 27:35.387
You mean watered it down?

27:35.387 --> 27:37.022
Whatever you want
to call it.

27:37.022 --> 27:38.557
You're upset because

27:38.557 --> 27:40.826
he talked like the
police commissioner

27:40.826 --> 27:42.261
and not your father.

27:42.261 --> 27:45.264
I don't see how he could've
handled it any other way.

27:45.264 --> 27:47.065
Of course you're gonna
take his side.

27:47.065 --> 27:48.734
I'm not taking sides.

27:48.734 --> 27:51.703
Why are you taking this
so personally?

27:53.805 --> 27:56.808
I can take the slings and arrows
from other attorneys

27:56.808 --> 27:58.810
and the D.A.
and even the press, but...

27:58.810 --> 28:00.312
But not your father?

28:00.312 --> 28:02.147
He was criticizing

28:02.147 --> 28:04.983
the D.A.'s office, not you.

28:04.983 --> 28:06.151
That's not what it felt like,

28:06.151 --> 28:08.654
and I was the one up there
taking the heat.

28:08.654 --> 28:10.956
You're confusing work
and family.

28:10.956 --> 28:13.358
Your father

28:13.358 --> 28:16.495
has the right to disagree
with the D.A.--

28:16.495 --> 28:18.263
yes, in public,

28:18.263 --> 28:21.800
and yes, even with you
standing there next to him--

28:21.800 --> 28:25.103
because it's his job.

28:25.103 --> 28:28.173
But no matter what happens,

28:28.173 --> 28:31.443
you'll always have his love
and support.

28:37.149 --> 28:39.518
Every time you leave the house,
you have to call first

28:39.518 --> 28:40.852
to say where you're going.

28:40.852 --> 28:42.187
If you're gonna be late
getting back

28:42.187 --> 28:43.388
or your train is delayed,

28:43.388 --> 28:44.990
your car breaks down,
you need to call us

28:44.990 --> 28:46.425
with the details.

28:46.425 --> 28:48.994
Then I should tell you
the coke and fentanyl exchange

28:48.994 --> 28:50.329
may be going down tonight.

28:50.329 --> 28:52.164
"May be going down tonight"?
I'll get a call

28:52.164 --> 28:53.765
this afternoon to confirm.

28:53.765 --> 28:54.866
Where?

28:54.866 --> 28:56.068
The old candy factory.

28:56.068 --> 28:57.936
I don't know how many people.

28:57.936 --> 29:00.672
Usually six or seven total.
Members of the Double Treys,

29:00.672 --> 29:03.008
Mano Sangriento, me.

29:03.008 --> 29:04.476
DANNY: Good. Now we know
where it's going down.

29:04.476 --> 29:06.612
So we don't need him to do this.

29:06.612 --> 29:08.981
Rojas expects me to be
there to handle the money.

29:08.981 --> 29:11.950
If he finds out I'm not,
he'll be in the wind.

29:11.950 --> 29:12.918
Don't trust him.

29:15.287 --> 29:17.623
Wipe that smile off your face.

29:17.623 --> 29:19.591
That's hard to do 'cause
you're so damn entertaining.

29:21.093 --> 29:22.094
Danny. Danny.
Reagan! Reagan!

29:23.261 --> 29:24.429
MOLINA:
Outside.

29:26.131 --> 29:28.467
Now!

29:28.467 --> 29:30.469
This is too personal for you

29:30.469 --> 29:32.904
and you cannot handle this...
It's not personal.

29:32.904 --> 29:34.940
I don't trust the son
of a bitch, okay?

29:34.940 --> 29:36.875
Well, we're on it.

29:36.875 --> 29:39.144
You don't know how
that guy works.
No?

29:39.144 --> 29:41.880
35 years ago,
my father crossed the border

29:41.880 --> 29:44.116
to get away
from Mano Sangriento.

29:44.116 --> 29:46.351
Okay, when he finally had
enough money,

29:46.351 --> 29:49.287
he went back to get the rest
of his family.

29:49.287 --> 29:53.158
Sangriento had killed
every last one of them.

29:53.158 --> 29:55.460
So...

29:55.460 --> 29:57.229
don't tell me I don't know him.

29:57.229 --> 29:59.264
Look, I'm sorry.

29:59.264 --> 30:01.199
I am.

30:02.601 --> 30:04.503
But you're playing with fire,
trusting this guy.

30:04.503 --> 30:06.004
You're the one playing
with fire,

30:06.004 --> 30:08.006
letting him get to you
like that.

30:08.006 --> 30:09.341
You either play by my rules,

30:09.341 --> 30:11.276
or you get the hell off my team.

30:32.197 --> 30:35.600
Okay. We got Delgado.

30:37.135 --> 30:39.171
Amigo.

31:04.362 --> 31:05.764
I know where you live.

31:05.764 --> 31:07.399
On my signal, we're gonna go.

31:09.334 --> 31:09.935
One.

31:11.903 --> 31:12.571
Two.

31:14.106 --> 31:15.474
Wait a minute.
Where the hell is he going?

31:15.474 --> 31:17.008
I don't know. His
car's in the front.

31:18.210 --> 31:19.444
What the hell is he doing?

31:19.444 --> 31:20.579
Three.
No. Wait.

31:20.579 --> 31:22.814
No, wait! No!
Go, go, go.

31:23.715 --> 31:25.784
Move, move!

31:25.784 --> 31:28.887
Hey. It's a setup. Hold on!

31:30.355 --> 31:31.289
Hey!

31:40.465 --> 31:43.401
Help! Help me! Help me!

31:43.401 --> 31:47.205
Come here, come here.

31:47.205 --> 31:49.274
Hang on!

31:52.244 --> 31:54.146
Baez, it's pepper spray!

32:00.619 --> 32:03.155
MAN:
It's pepper spray!

32:17.269 --> 32:19.171
Delgado?!

32:29.581 --> 32:31.516
Delgado?

32:47.966 --> 32:49.901
Aah!

33:17.128 --> 33:19.197
It's a didgeridoo.

33:19.197 --> 33:22.100
An Australian wind instrument,
a little bit like a trumpet.

33:22.100 --> 33:24.102
Oh.

33:24.102 --> 33:26.538
Thank you.

33:26.538 --> 33:29.541
It's a gift from
the prime minister of Australia

33:29.541 --> 33:31.076
for hosting him last week.

33:31.076 --> 33:35.480
A donation to the NYPD Museum?

33:36.748 --> 33:39.417
Brian's doing better.

33:39.417 --> 33:42.187
He is, thank you.

33:42.187 --> 33:44.389
Thought you weren't coming in
for a few weeks.

33:44.389 --> 33:47.092
I told Jimmy
I'd relieve him for a few hours.

33:47.092 --> 33:48.426
I could use the break.

33:48.426 --> 33:51.663
Things are bad
if work's a break.

33:51.663 --> 33:53.999
Actually, things are very good.

33:53.999 --> 33:56.201
Brian is breathing on his own,

33:56.201 --> 33:58.336
he's complaining
about hospital food,

33:58.336 --> 34:01.239
and they're gonna release him
tomorrow.

34:02.340 --> 34:04.342
Good news.

34:04.342 --> 34:06.144
Well, maybe you should

34:06.144 --> 34:08.246
rethink that no-smile policy.

34:13.952 --> 34:17.756
I have accompanied you
on many, many hospital visits

34:17.756 --> 34:21.459
to officers who have been
injured in the line of duty,

34:21.459 --> 34:24.663
some who have died
in the line of duty.

34:24.663 --> 34:27.232
I knew it was your job.

34:27.232 --> 34:31.336
What I never fully understood
was just how important

34:31.336 --> 34:34.306
your visit is
to the officer's family.

34:40.245 --> 34:42.180
And now I know.

34:43.548 --> 34:45.550
Thank you.

34:57.862 --> 35:00.966
Son of a bitch, he set us up.
I told you not to trust him.

35:00.966 --> 35:02.233
We don't know that yet.

35:02.233 --> 35:03.635
Of course he set us up.

35:03.635 --> 35:06.037
He got the hell out of there
right before the boxes exploded.

35:06.037 --> 35:08.506
How the hell would he know?!
He knew what was coming.

35:08.506 --> 35:11.376
Then why did he go back
to his apartment?
What?

35:12.510 --> 35:13.845
Look at the ankle monitor.

35:13.845 --> 35:15.480
It proves that he's there.

35:15.480 --> 35:17.148
Then, what happened?

35:17.148 --> 35:19.284
Well, I'll let you
know after I see him.
No, no, no, no.

35:19.284 --> 35:20.919
You'll let 'em know
after we see him.

35:20.919 --> 35:22.187
We're going with you.

35:27.592 --> 35:29.127
Let's go.

35:37.769 --> 35:40.305
Delgado? Police!

35:40.305 --> 35:42.540
I thought the GPS said
he was here.

35:42.540 --> 35:44.042
It did.

35:44.042 --> 35:46.277
It's Agent Molina, Luis.

35:46.277 --> 35:47.712
We need to talk to you.

35:47.712 --> 35:48.847
Luis?

35:48.847 --> 35:50.115
DELGADO:
Please, come in.

35:58.990 --> 36:01.860
You know, I'm glad you came.

36:01.860 --> 36:03.228
Something I've been wanting
to tell you.

36:03.228 --> 36:06.898
What's that?
You know your wife's
helicopter accident?

36:06.898 --> 36:08.233
It really wasn't an accident.

36:08.233 --> 36:10.101
It was all arranged
by Mano Sangriento,

36:10.101 --> 36:12.771
because you started
playing games with them.

36:18.043 --> 36:19.411
You son of a bitch.
Where the hell are you?

36:19.411 --> 36:20.712
Where are you?!

36:20.712 --> 36:22.547
DELGADO:
You really shouldn't
play games with them.

36:22.547 --> 36:23.581
And do you know why?

36:23.581 --> 36:25.116
I don't give a damn why.

36:25.116 --> 36:27.452
DELGADO:
Because they always win.

36:28.753 --> 36:30.755
Where are you, Delgado?

36:36.928 --> 36:39.497
Real tough guy, huh?

36:39.497 --> 36:40.732
Couldn't come face me?

36:40.732 --> 36:42.600
Oh, I am facing you, Detective.

36:42.600 --> 36:45.970
And you know what I see?
A loser.

36:45.970 --> 36:49.407
Now, if you'll excuse me, I'm
gonna go mix myself a drink.

36:51.843 --> 36:53.578
I'll get TARU in here,
run a trace on the video.

36:53.578 --> 36:54.913
You told me
the GPS said he was here.

36:54.913 --> 36:56.815
The son of a bitch isn't here!

36:56.815 --> 36:59.084
It said that he was here.

37:13.732 --> 37:15.667
LENA:
Good one.

37:16.901 --> 37:18.136
Hello?

37:18.136 --> 37:19.537
Hey.

37:19.537 --> 37:21.239
Eddie, uh, Mom and I--

37:21.239 --> 37:22.574
we made dinner for you.

37:22.574 --> 37:24.576
My mom doesn't cook.
What did I

37:24.576 --> 37:25.910
always tell you, Edit?

37:25.910 --> 37:27.512
"Forget the dishes on the shelf,

37:27.512 --> 37:28.847
be a tasty dish yourself"?

37:30.081 --> 37:33.551
So, we ordered takeout
from Balthazar's.

37:34.919 --> 37:36.087
Want some wine?

37:36.087 --> 37:37.388
Mm-hmm.

37:37.388 --> 37:38.656
Okay.

37:42.427 --> 37:44.929
She ordered from the most
expensive restaurant,

37:44.929 --> 37:46.765
and we are gonna
foot the bill.

37:46.765 --> 37:49.000
Yeah, I know.
You know?

37:49.000 --> 37:50.468
What were you thinking?

37:50.468 --> 37:52.537
I thought it would be good
to make amends.

37:52.537 --> 37:54.172
She brought the
family photo album?

37:54.172 --> 37:55.707
Well, that was my idea.

37:55.707 --> 37:57.542
Does it get better
if she has a few drinks?

37:57.542 --> 37:59.844
Well, it gets better if we do.

38:01.880 --> 38:04.382
Edit, your first bikini!

38:04.382 --> 38:06.351
It's a good thing
you grew some boobs after that.

38:08.019 --> 38:09.621
Who was that guy
that you went with?

38:09.621 --> 38:10.955
What was his name?

38:10.955 --> 38:12.423
Oh. Stan.

38:12.423 --> 38:13.958
Stan. That's right.

38:13.958 --> 38:16.861
His father was a cardiologist.

38:16.861 --> 38:18.530
What ever happened to him?
Well,

38:18.530 --> 38:21.499
Mom, uh, Stan became
a cardiologist, too,

38:21.499 --> 38:23.568
and he lives in Boca.

38:23.568 --> 38:25.003
Ah.
Oh. Nice boy.

38:25.003 --> 38:27.705
I'll have a refill.
Yeah.

38:27.705 --> 38:31.176
Mom, you scared off every boy
I ever brought home.

38:31.176 --> 38:35.380
If they were all scared off,
then none of them deserve you.

38:35.380 --> 38:37.415
Is that your excuse?

38:37.415 --> 38:38.783
It's true.

38:38.783 --> 38:41.386
They all ran, except for one.

38:45.123 --> 38:47.926
He's the only one who came back.

39:04.008 --> 39:06.010
I love you.

39:06.010 --> 39:07.645
Something wrong?

39:07.645 --> 39:09.681
No.

39:11.616 --> 39:14.252
LENA:
You've got

39:14.252 --> 39:15.386
to see this, Jamie.

39:15.386 --> 39:17.822
Eddie dressed as
Jessica Rabbit

39:17.822 --> 39:19.724
for Halloween.

39:19.724 --> 39:21.726
Ooh, I actually look
pretty hot in that one.

39:21.726 --> 39:23.661
Well, what are we waiting for?
Mm.

39:42.280 --> 39:44.449
You already put the bait on?

39:44.449 --> 39:46.985
Thought I'd save
you the trouble.
It's a blood worm?

39:46.985 --> 39:48.886
Sand worms.

39:48.886 --> 39:51.389
I would have gone
with herring.

39:51.389 --> 39:53.758
You want me to put
on a bottom bait?

39:53.758 --> 39:56.928
No, I didn't ask you to come
out here to valet the tackle.

39:56.928 --> 39:58.863
Okay.

40:01.032 --> 40:04.068
You know how old you were
when I taught you to fish?

40:04.068 --> 40:06.004
No.
Seven.

40:06.004 --> 40:08.539
Actually, I wasn't
gonna teach you at all,

40:08.539 --> 40:10.675
even though I
taught the boys.

40:10.675 --> 40:13.645
Because I was a girl?

40:13.645 --> 40:15.880
No.

40:15.880 --> 40:18.249
Because it is
the kind of activity

40:18.249 --> 40:20.985
where even
if you do everything perfectly,

40:20.985 --> 40:23.821
there's no guarantee of a fish.

40:23.821 --> 40:27.859
And what else is like that,
if I'm hearing you correctly?

40:27.859 --> 40:30.895
Being a boss.

40:30.895 --> 40:35.166
One slipup, and the searchlight
comes on hot and fast.

40:35.166 --> 40:37.302
Tell me about it.

40:39.404 --> 40:42.573
Pop told me I took
the press conference personally.

40:42.573 --> 40:45.143
That I was expecting
you'd act more like

40:45.143 --> 40:47.078
a protective father
than the PC.

40:47.078 --> 40:49.113
And what do you think?

40:49.113 --> 40:52.517
That my mistake was acting
like a respectful daughter,

40:52.517 --> 40:55.053
letting you have the last word.

40:58.222 --> 41:00.224
And the next time?

41:00.224 --> 41:03.461
I will always
be respectful of you.

41:03.461 --> 41:06.464
Couldn't be
any other way, but...

41:06.464 --> 41:09.100
I need to respect
my office, too.

41:13.538 --> 41:17.642
And maybe keep the joint press
conferences to a minimum.

41:17.642 --> 41:20.678
Yeah. That, too.

41:22.246 --> 41:24.482
Ooh.

41:24.482 --> 41:27.085
Well, what do you know.

41:27.085 --> 41:29.020
Results.
